message.content: A 35-year-old African American female with a history of asthma presents with shortness of breath, cough, and fatigue, and is found to have bilateral hilar lymphadenopathy on chest X-ray, consistent with sarcoidosis.

A 32 year old African American female presents with shortness of breath, fatigue, and non-specific chest pain, with a past medical history of asthma and hypertension. Chest X-ray shows bilateral hilar lymphadenopathy and pulmonary infiltrates. Sarcoidosis is suspected.

A 35-year-old African American female with a history of asthma presents with complaints of shortness of breath, cough, and chest pain, and is found to have bilateral hilar lymphadenopathy and noncaseating granulomas on biopsy, consistent with sarcoidosis.

A 35-year-old African American female with no significant past medical history presents with shortness of breath, fatigue, and a dry cough, with imaging showing bilateral hilar lymphadenopathy and diffuse pulmonary infiltrates, consistent with sarcoidosis.
